preparation_steps: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat and cook onion, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes or until tender. Remove onion from skillet and let cool.

Combine ground beef, zucchini, egg, cooked onion, remaining 2 tablespoons jalapeno peppers, 1/2 cup sauce mixture and black pepper in large bowl. Shape into loaf in 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan. Top with 1/2 cup sauce mixture.

Meanwhile, bring Pasta Sauce and 2 tablespoons jalapeno peppers to a boil over high heat in same skillet. Reduce heat to low and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes. Stir in 2 tablespoons cilantro; set aside.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons cilantro and garnish, if desired, with additional pickled jalapenos. Serve with hot rice and remaining sauce mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

Stir-Fry Beef and Broccoli
preparation_steps: In a medium bowl, whisk together hoison sauce through red pepper flakes. Add meat to bowl and marinate for about 15 minutes. Meanwhile, prepare the vegetables.

In a large wok, heat 1 tablespoon of oil over medium-high heat and add beef strips. Cook until browned, about 2-3 minutes, being careful not to overcook. Reserve the leftover marinade. Remove beef from wok and set aside.

Add 1 tablespoon of oil to wok over medium-high heat. Add onion, peppers, garlic, and ginger, stirring for about 4 minutes until fragrant. Stir in the broccoli florets and cook until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Toss in the beef strips and leftover marinade. Cook another 1-2 minutes until heated through. Serve over brown rice. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds.
recipes.description: This classic stir-fry dish is perfect for beef and broccoli lovers. It's simple, flavorful and packs a punch!

recipes.name: Beef and Mushroom Stir-Fry
preparation_steps: Mix beef sirloin, crushed garlic, Worcestershire sauce, rice vinegar, grated peeled fresh ginger, and cornstarch in large bowl.

Heat canola oil in 12-inch wok or skillet over high heat. Add sliced mushrooms and stir-fry 2 minutes or until browned. Add beef mixture and stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until almost dry. Stir in beef broth, green onions, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened.
Serve beef mixture over white rice, warmed, with lime wedges.

Croatian Style Stuffed Peppers With A Twist
preparation_steps: Cook the rice and leave it aside to cool. Cut the onion and garlic cloves, heat the skillet over medium, pour 2 tablespoons of olive oil. When the oil is hot, add onion and garlic. Stir occasionally and when they turn golden/brown, add beef,  tbsp of chilli powder,  ½ tbsp of cumin, salt and pepper. If you need, add a litle bit of water (1 dcl) for meat to soften faster.

When the meat is half cooked, add rice, beans, tomato sauce and ½ teaspoon of hot sauce. I put just a little bit cause I don't like it very very spicy, but you can put more if u like it  Lower the heat, add 1 dcl water, mix everything and let it simmer for 10 min. Preheat the oven at 200°C.
Meanwhile, take out the insides of peppers and wash them. I like to sprinkle it with salt and pepper just to taste before I put them in the oven. Place them into brass and sprinkle with olive oil.

When the meat is done, fill the peppers and put them into oven for 15-20 min. I usually put grated cheese on top as well, it tastes great when is baked and the melted cheese all over the peppers is just mmm! :)
recipes.description:
I am a little bit nostalgic these days for Croatia, my hometown, friends and family. I really miss them and my life in Croatia, but I'm not complaining! We all have those moments, now it's my turn to have it. So to comfort myself and bring a little bit of Croatia here in France, I decided to make this dish.
Stuffed peppers is the basic meal in every Croatian family, for real! I remember, when I was a primary school kid, my mom would made it during the weekends. Not every weekend, but during the winter it was part of our menu very often. Also, when I would visit my friends at their house, I would see that even their moms prepare it! This dish is a part of our culture and tradition, but every region in Croatia has different way to prepare it, and they are all good!
The thing with the Croatian cuisine is that really every region has it's own specialities, meals, different ways of preparing food with same ingredients. Every region has something to be proud of. For example my region, Istria, is known for truffles and the mighty „Maneštra“, Dalmatia for basically all the meals based on seafood and so on.. 
Originally, stuffed peppers have to cook for some time, and the preparation is a bit harder than my recipe, but since today we all want to shorten the time for cooking during the working days, I came up with the recipe below! :D

You can check it as well on my blog: https://jaysfoodventure.com/

Sweet Thai Chili Steak Bowls
preparation_steps: Season your skirt steak generously, on both sides, with salt and pepper. Let the steak sit on the counter (away from pets if you have them) while you prep the other ingredients.

Add the Thai Chile sauce, soy sauce, peanut butter, orange juice, rice vinegar, lime juice, garlic, and grated ginger into a bowl. Whisk. The peanut butter may not incorporate well at this stage, but don't worry, you'll be cooking (which will help melt the peanut butter) later in this recipe.  This will be your Sweet Thai Chili Sauce.

Heat a splash of your favorite high smoke point oil (like peanut, corn, or vegetable oil) in a skillet over medium-high heat. Sear both sides of the skirt steak until you reach your favorite doneness. I prefer medium rare, so mine cook a few minutes per side.

Pull the cooked steak out of the skillet, place it on a plate, cover with tin foil. Turn down the heat in the pan to medium. Add additional oil (if necessary) and your garlic cloves. Your pan will be HOT from cooking the steak, even though you just turned down the heat. The moment you add the garlic, stir it around a couple of times, but then immediately add your onion, carrot, red pepper, and jalapeño. Sweat the vegetables until they soften, approx 5 minutes.

Pour the Sweet Chili Sauce into the pan with the vegetables and stir until everything is well combined. Bring the sauce to a boil, turn down the heat to low, and simmer for 5- 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Once the sauce is finished simmering, you can eat! Slice up your steak into strips.
Portion your rice until bowls, top the rice with the sweet chili sauce/vegetable mixture, and top that with sliced steak. Sprinkle with your favorite garnishes and enjoy!
recipes.description: Sweet Thai Chili Steak Bowls, it's the perfect balance of sweet and spicy!  I used steak but this recipe would still be fantastic if you used either chicken or tofu!

preparation_steps: Preheat oven to 375°.

Brown ground beef with green peppers and chili powder in deep 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until peppers are tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in 1 cup salsa, cooked rice and 1/2 cup cheese.
Turn beef mixture into 8-inch baking dish. Combine remaining salsa with Hellmann's® or Best Foods® Real Mayonnaise in small bowl. Pour over beef mixture.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until golden.
